[[How to map paths from foundamental group with one base point to another with another base point, given a path connecting them|https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Lcu93_AfTQw&list=PLLq_gUfXAnkl8bjQh-hGQ9u24xZP9x0dx&index=16#t=41m40s]]. Shows that the groups are [[isomorphic|Group isomorphism]].

[[Therefore|https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Lcu93_AfTQw&list=PLLq_gUfXAnkl8bjQh-hGQ9u24xZP9x0dx&index=16#t=52m24s]], if $$X$$ is [[Path connected]], then all fundamental groups are isomorphic. However, in general, there is not a canonical/natural isomorphism, it depends on the path. See [[this other vid|https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uBDYSPMyaRQ&list=PLLq_gUfXAnkkdRttylq7Svmob1gxDgcDZ#t=53m]]

